## Forms

### Waitlist Form Pattern

```typescript
// src/components/sections/waitlist.tsx
import { useForm } from "@tanstack/react-form";
import { zodValidator } from "@tanstack/zod-form-adapter";
import { z } from "zod";
import { joinWaitlist } from "~/lib/actions";

const schema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email("Please enter a valid email"),
});

export function WaitlistForm() {
  const form = useForm({
    defaultValues: { email: "" },
    validatorAdapter: zodValidator(),
    onSubmit: async ({ value }) => {
      await joinWaitlist({ data: value });
    },
  });

  return (
    <form
      onSubmit={(e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        form.handleSubmit();
      }}
      className="flex gap-3"
    >
      <form.Field name="email">
        {(field) => (
          <input
            type="email"
            placeholder="Enter your email address"
            value={field.state.value}
            onChange={(e) => field.handleChange(e.target.value)}
            className="flex-1 px-4 py-3 bg-card border border-border rounded-lg"
          />
        )}
      </form.Field>
      <button type="submit" className="px-6 py-3 bg-primary rounded-lg font-medium">
        Join Waitlist
      </button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Accessibility Requirements

- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use semantic HTML (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- Provide alt text for decorative images or mark as `aria-hidden`
- Ensure color contrast ratios meet WCAG 2.1 AA (4.5:1 for text)
- Focus indicators must be visible
- Skip links for main content navigation

## Performance Guidelines

- Lazy load below-fold images
- Use `loading="lazy"` on images
- Optimize and compress all assets
- Self-host fonts with `font-display: swap`
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size
- Use CSS for animations where possible
- Preload critical assets

